    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften </p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mussel-and-king-prawn-risotto-ai-frutti-di-mare/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain your <strong>mussels </strong>in a sieve over a large bowl, reserve the <strong>juices</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>mussel juices</strong> with 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> fish stock</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mussel-and-king-prawn-risotto-ai-frutti-di-mare/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the shallot has started to soften, add your <strong>arborio rice</strong>, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>and<strong> tomato paste </strong>and cook for 30 secs min further or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mussel-and-king-prawn-risotto-ai-frutti-di-mare/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>fish stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 20-25 min or until most of the stock is absorbed and the rice is nearly cooked</p><p>Tip: Your rice will be slightly al dente and there will be a little stock left!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mussel-and-king-prawn-risotto-ai-frutti-di-mare/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mussel-and-king-prawn-risotto-ai-frutti-di-mare/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is nearly cooked, stir through a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper </strong>with <strong>half</strong> your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Drain, then add your<strong> king prawns </strong>with a knob of<strong> butter </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mussel-and-king-prawn-risotto-ai-frutti-di-mare/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top with the <strong>drained mussels </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid and cook for a further 5-6 min or until the prawns and mussels are cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>mussel & king prawn risotto ai frutti di mare</strong></p><p>Tip: Discard any mussels which shells have not opened!</p><p>Set aside the <strong>mussel & king prawn risotto ai frutti di mare</strong>, with the lid on, for 2-3 min for the flavours to develop</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mussel-and-king-prawn-risotto-ai-frutti-di-mare/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> mussel & king prawn risotto ai frutti di mare </strong>and top with the<strong> remaining parsley </strong>and <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
